HEADWORD: Water clock
<hw>Wa"ter clock`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>An instrument or machine
serving to measure time by the fall, or flow, of a certain quantity of
water; a clepsydra.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water-closet</ent>⟦br⟧
